Hey everyone
Presenting before you a radio drama by us @pro_is_a_gremlin @framebysam and me

Special thanks to @adarsh_aryan_18 for giving voice to Ishwari and to @gs_can.v for giving voice to Veer!

Thank you so much to @ashwini4ashwini for singing so commendably and giving another layer to Veer's thoughts at such a short notice :)
And also playing the dhaba owner

Nasha is a story by Munshi Premchand wherein he beautifully shows the internal dilemma of Veer who is the son of a clerk as he compares himself to Ishwari who belongs to a family of Zamindars. Tried our best to do justice to the story!

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Karimul Haque is a worker in the tea gardens of West Bengal. Locally known as Bike-Ambulance-dada, he has received the Padma Shri award for his work supporting the villagers in and around Dhalabari by bringing sick people to hospital in his motorcycle ambulance.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Healing Himalayas - Earth Day special
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
today is earth day and on this day I bring to u the story of Pradeep sangwan! Every year in December, Pradeep designs a calendar for the following year, listing out all the weekend treks. He has been trekking for more than a decade and a few years ago, he felt he couldn’t be a passive spectator to the plastic and glass being discarded in tourist pockets of Himachal Pradesh.

He registered the Healing Himalayas Foundation in 2016 and got to work. “The first six months were relegated to streamlining the process — of how to collect and manage the waste,” he recalls.

The treks usually begin in Shimla in March, gauging the snowfall and weather conditions. In April, treks are conducted to higher altitudes such as the Parashar Lake, nearly 50 kilometres north of Mandi, in Himachal Pradesh. The lake’s vicinity draws visitors for a pagoda-like temple structure, but in recent years has also become a popular camping and partying zone, posing waste management issues. In May, the treks are towards further higher zones of the Kheerganga.
